Description

China-nexus covert proxy networks using large scale IoT botnets (e.g., Raptor Train) to enable stealthy, persistent cyber operations and evade traditional detection.
Defensive Guidance:
Baseline Controls (All Organizations):
Enforce multi-factor authentication (MFA)
Map and baseline internet-facing assets
Monitor VPN and remote access traffic
Use dynamic threat intelligence feeds
Reduce unnecessary internet exposure
Intermediate Controls (Moderate Risk):
Implement IP allow lists
Apply geographic filtering
Introduce behavioral traffic analysis
Deploy Zero Trust principles
Use SSL/TLS machine certificate validation
Advanced Controls (High-Risk/Large Organizations):
Active threat hunting for covert network activity
NetFlow analysis for traffic pattern anomalies
Integration of dynamic block lists and alerting
Tracking evolving attacker infrastructure
Machine learning-based anomaly detection
